t5319.text: 5/5 then what do you do? @Scamwatch_gov has some great info on how to better protect yourself from future email scams how to report them how to get help if you think you fell for the scam. you can also sign up to their scam alert servicehttps://www.scamwatch.gov.au/news/subscribe-to-scam-alert-emails …

t5320.text: 4/5 What can you do if you get one of these emails? Do not open any attachments or click on links from emails claiming to be from your bank or another trusted organisation and asking you to update or verify your details – just press delete

t5321.text: 3/5 What happens when people click on the link or open the attachment? - It may take you to a fake website in the hope you will enter your log in details (your credentials ) Or - it may download bad software that could sit on your computer & ‘harvest’ your credentials

t5322.text: 2/5 What are the criminals doing with all of these messages/URLs etc? They’ve been sending #malicious emails aka #phishing emails to -Claim a member of staff had been infected/your neighbour has tested positive OR - pretend to be the WHO & then try to get you to click....

t5323.text: 1/5 #EmailSecurity co. #Proofpoint have tracked #Covid19 related #malicious #activity since 29.01.20.
